<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Manchester City defender Angelino will return to RB Leipzig after spending the second half of last season on loan at the club.</p>

<p>The left-back joined the Bundesliga club in January and impressed by scoring once and registering five assists in 18 appearances for Julian Nagelsmann's side. </p>

<p>Leipzig have re-signed the 23-year-old on a season-long loan that will include an appearance-based obligation to buy for £16million. </p>

<p>Manchester City defender Angelino will return to RB Leipzig for a season-long loan next term</p>

<p>The obligation to buy will be triggered if Angelino makes 12 appearances for the club, with five of those coming in the second half of the season. </p>

<p>Should Leipzig chose to feature Angelino for the stipulated number of game, the club will land the Spaniard permanently on a four-year deal until 2025.  </p>

<p>Speaking of the deal, Angelino told RB Leipzig's official website that he is delighted to have put pen to paper with the Bundesliga club. </p>

<p>'I'm delighted to be staying in Leipzig and that we carry on our journey together.'</p>

<p>However, his loan deal does contain an obligation to buy for £16m at the end of the season</p>

<p>He scored once and registered five assists in 18 appearances for Julian Nagelsmann's side</p>

<p>'My first six months with RBL have been amazing; I got lots of game time straightaway and I really like the coach and the team's approach.</p>

<p>'We also had really successful Bundesliga and Champions League campaigns. I'm very much looking forward to the future and lots more success.'</p>

<p>While, RB Leipzig sporting director Markus Krosche added: 'Angel hasn't needed much time to settle in with us and he's understood our brand of football from the start.</p>

<p>'He did really well in the Ruckrunde and also helped us achieve our goals in the Champions League. </p>

<p>'He's made a great impact with us. That's why we're so pleased that he'll be wearing an RB Leipzig shirt for at least another season.'</p>

<p>Angelino is likely to feature for Leipzig on September 20 when they host Mainz and play an ever present role in their 2020-2021 European campaign. </p>
